Commentary Text: Nadeem to Shahbaz Ahmed, out Caught by Rashid Khan!! That's a superb running catch from Rashid - ran across a long way to his right from deep backward square leg, slides and pulls off a superb effort - Shahbaz, at three, hasn't quite worked out for the RCBs. Came down the track, got too close to the ball and didn't get the needed elevation the lofted on-drive, dragged it behind square on the on-side - could have dropped down safely, if not for Rashid. Commentary Text: Shahbaz Ahmed to Manish Pandey, out Caught by Harshal Patel!! This is just rush of blood. Samad has been sent to do the big hitting. As a set batter you are expected to bat till the end on such a difficult surface for newcomers and Pandey throws it away. He backed himself to get a maximum and ease pressure. Ran down the pitch, but an alert Shahbaz Ahmed fired this wide of off stump and forced Pandey to fetch the ball. Pandey had second thoughts about it and he ended up toe-ending it high to short third man. On a hat-trick. Manish Pandey c Harshal Patel b Shahbaz Ahmed 38(39) [4s-2 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Jamieson to Warner, out Caught by Christian!! The change works for Kohli, A furious Warner punches his bat hard and walks off. Simplicity works in Chennai. Just drop it into the wicket and offer no pace, force the batsman to do all the work and get the rewards. It may seem like a rank long hop but on a sticky wicket, those with no pace are really difficult to get away. Warner went for the slap, hit it straight down long-on throat and that's just the opening RCB wanted. Now then.. Who's at the door? Warner c Christian b Jamieson 54(37) [4s-7 6s-1]
